tags.description: Mining town named for the mercury mine near which it is built; published in 1950 by USGS. A post office was established here in 1957.

tags.description: Name reported in 1923; so called because the trail from Ruby to Poorman crossed the Sulatna River at this point.

tags.name: Atqasuk
tags.note: The Dictionary of Alaska Place Names lists Meade River as the proper name of this place. Atkasuk and Atkasak are listed as variations. Atqusuk is perhaps a more modern or more ethnically correct spelling of these variations.
tags.source:alt_name: Dictionary of Alaska Place Names, Orth, 1967
